Listing 4-2 Using alias with Count function

from django.db.models import Count
 
books = Book.objects.alias(
    total_genres=Count("genres")
).filter(total_genres__gt=1)
 
Equivalent SQL

SELECT book.id, book.title, book.author_id, book.price,
book.number_of_pages, book.published_date,
book.created_at
FROM book
LEFT OUTER JOIN book_genres
ON book.id = book_genres.book_id
GROUP BY book.id
HAVING COUNT(book_genres.genre_id) > 1;